Holidays are often associated with church holidays, historical events.
We also celebrate the New Year: the last day of the year and the first day of the new year are both off - the latter just to give holidaymakers a break.
We have 11 red letter celebrations all year round, by the way.
It is a national holiday commemorating the revolution of 1848 on 15 March and also on 23 October, the anniversary of the 1956 revolution.
On August 20, we celebrate the founding of the state, on May 1, we celebrate the work, and on November 1 and 2, we remember our deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, we have two days of Easter, Easter, and Christmas.
